message.entry: First input must be a function handle.
Group numbers must be a vector of positive integers, and cannot be a sparse vector.

The data variables must have the same number of rows as the vector of group numbers. The group number vector has {0,number,integer} row(s), and data variable {1,number,integer} has {2,number,integer} row(s).

The data variables must have the same number of columns as the vector of group numbers. The group number vector has {0,number,integer} column(s), and data variable {1,number,integer} has {2,number,integer} column(s).
Unable to apply the function ''{0}'' to the {1} group of data.
For N groups, every integer between 1 and N must occur at least once in the vector of group numbers.
